<h1>Problem 2222 - 2025 EGMO, P2 of 6, AC</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>An infinite increasing sequence \(a_1 < a_2 < a_3 < \dots\) of positive integers is called central if for every positive integer \(n\), the arithmetic mean of the first \(a_n\) terms of the sequence is equal to \(a_n\).</p>
<p>Show that there exists an infinite sequence \(b_1\), \(b_2\), \(b_3\), \(\dots\) of positive integers such that for every central sequence \(a_1\), \(a_2\), \(a_3\), \(\dots\), there are infinitely many positive integers \(n\) with \(a_n = b_n\).</p>
